I have a simple function defined for a health check, its coming in from API Gateway but it is a very simple file that looks like this:

```php
<?php

try {
    (new PDO($dsn, $user, $password))
        ->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE, PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION);

    echo 'everything is good to go';
} catch (PDOException $e) {
    echo 'something went wrong';
}
```

In this case, I don't _need_ the vendor autoload but the default php-fpm layer is always attempting to load. 

Would a similar approach taken in #556 of adding an environment variable like `BREF_DISABLE_AUTOLOAD` make sense?

